inn1.comm: starts with a very wide outside off, not quite a Harmison, but still
better line, down the channel on a good length, the batsman shoulders arms
outside off, pushes into the covers where Symonds fields well, dives and underarms to Clarke around the gully, who throws back in
shoulders arms again as the ball whistles down the channel again, short and rising up, with some more swing
boomed outside off at 143kph again, but a touch too wide to prompt the shot, this one a leave
some more width outside off and chopped away through Symonds and Clarke, the ball racing through point and Tendulkar declines a third, though they may have made it
the first ball of the over that forces the batsman to play, the ball tight just outside off and defended back down
stays over the wicket to the right hander, can't nail the line, the ball too straight and Tendulkar helps it off the legs behind square and they scurry through
straight this time, Uthappa comes across his stumps, looking to turn it off the hips but doesn't quite time
outside the legs this time, a shortish ball that's worked off the pads square now
pushed behind square to short square leg where Hussey picks up and shies down the non-striker's stumps, the richochet allowing the batsmen to run through
on middle and leg, pushed out well to midwicket and again they run through
swing back in to him from off to middle and the batsman defends on the front foot
the ball carries through on a good length, Tendulkar just lets it go, and that's a good piece of judgement as it nips back in off the seam and just jumps over the sticks
well bowled by Lee, at 145kph, drawing him into the shot, a front-foot defensive press away from his body and the ball is that far from taking the outside edge
it's all action out there, Tendulkar this time presses forward, the ball goes down from a good length, hits the bat and dives into the crease and then goes behind towards the keeper
another good-length ball, again on off, in line with the stumps this time and he plays forward
yet again makes him defend, on the back foot this time, in line with off stump
Lee now gives him a window of room outside off and Tendulkar drives out through the covers, a release of the pressure at last
fired across the right hander on a tight line, just outside off, the batsman waits on the back foot and turns the face of the blade out towards point
some curve back into the batsman but brings the ball too straight and there's a clip off the legs in line with leg stump out to midwicket
that's better insofar as it's not on the legs, but aimed wider and the batsman left it on the back foot, not interested
on middle this time, a good length, squeezed into short midwicket off the back foot and in comes an urgent "Waiting, waiting, waiting."
just outside off this time, but the batsman can leave very comfortably indeed
down the channel, on a good length, but the batsman isn't tempted by one which pitches just outside the line of off, waiting on his back foot as he considers what to do
a hint of width outside off, drawing the batsman into a slash towards the off-side, missing the ball
down leg and the batsman's on to it quickly, the crowd fast in response too, but his firm pull from a short one goes straight to the man at deep backward square leg
phew, too good there, perfect length, full and drew him forward for a press just outside off and failed to get the outside edge
a short one this time, outside off, Tendulkar's first and final instinct is to sway back and leave. Watch out because he rehearsed the pull immediately afterwards
a full one, wide, and carrying wider down off
outside off, short ball, curving out a touch, Tendulkar pushes off the back foot into the covers with a hint of attack
forced across him on a line and length which forces him to walk over a touch and defend on the back foot
a tad straighter this time, again a good length, and the batsman defends once again
taken from middle and off, the batsman getting into the line and forcing it off the front foot to Hussey just behind square who pinches it and throws back in
outside off this time, the batsman drives off the back foot into the covers
quite wide across him, the batsman leaves that one on the back foot as it comes through on a good length, rising up
overpitched a touch outside off, the batsman latches on to it with a drives out to cover where it's cut off for a mere single

short ball on middle and leg, pulls hard behind square and Bracken, fresh from bowling, comes round and dives out hard to cut it off well. Top marks for the fielding, including a rocket of a throw back to Gilchrist
Bracken's off in pursuit again as the batsman helps the short one on leg squarer this time, five metres or so too far away from the fielder
very full delivery, a would-be yorker on off, Uthappa stabs down on it, angling the face out towards third man, Hopes does the fielding down there
short outside off, driven out in front of point with a firm push, Symonds stops it well
back of a length just outside off, the batsman punches out back straight
a full delivery on off, the batsman is firm in defence this time
on the legs, turned out in front of square where Hussey is vigilant and quick with the return throw
dropped. A hard chance by Ponting, good placement by himself though, and he got both hands there as the bowler puts in a wide one and it's lashed hard to him at the short cover region
defended on the front foot this time
on middle and off, defended back down into the ground, not much fuss about that delivery
outside off, defended down off the back foot to the covers
outside off, a touch wide, cut down off the back foot to Hayden in the slips who stops it well
oh, nearly dragged back on an inside edge, the batsman keen to make the most of some width outside off and he tried to pull it to midwicket
outside off, drives on the up through the covers, good placement
slower ball nearly gets the result, a good near-yorker which swings out, the batsman comes down, pushes, and takes the outside edge out towards third man
shot of the day which is but young of course, short ball outside off, Tendulkar cuts hard off the back foot, upper-cutting it wide and out towards third man
outside off, the batsman waits for the wideish one and cuts late down once more, a bit squarer this time
a short one, just outside off, the batsman waits on the back foot and exploits the gap between the slips and point, running the ball down to third man
a huge appeal for one which raps him on the pads in line with leg, Taufel turns it down, suggesting it pitched outside - and it was marginal
pushed across him outside off this time, the ball hurries on outside off, and is turned down to short third man
again across him, fuller length, and the batsman defends hard on the front foot
a full delivery outside off, pulled round through deep midwicket, not quite timing that off the base of the bat
a full delivery again, also on off, this time the choice is a drive to the covers
some swing again, on middle and leg, and squeezed out easily to midwicket
turned off the legs to midwicket for a comfortable single
outside off, defended back down on the front foot, reasonable length
on middle, the batsman comes across his stumps a touch to open up the leg-side and drive in front of midwicket
short ball outside off, the bowler gets away with it as it's lashed to point, Clarke picks up and throws back in quickly
rolls his fingers over that one, a touch of room outside off, angled down to third man
width outside off, guided out wide down to third man
aims one a touch down leg, the batsman goes to tuck it off the hips and nearly strangles it through to the keeper
a touch wide down leg this time, Johnson forcing it just too much from over the wicket, by the way
the ball swings in just a touch, late and full on off, pushed out defensively
a lone appeal this time
down leg for another leg-side wide
short ball outside off, better line now, and the batsman defends back down off the back foot
on middle and off, good length again, defended back down
short ball outside off, cut down through point
straight ball on middle, the ball brushes down off the gloves into the off-side, they think about the single but decide not to go for it
quality timing for one which is played uppishly from outside off through mid-on for four off a mere push
some width outside off, not much mind, the batsman opens his arms and looks to turn it back out through point
a hint of room outside off, cut down behind point and the fifty partnership has come up now
outside off, some width there on a short one, cut hard off the back foot to Clarke at the gully, the ball bouncing three or four times before he clamps down on it with a dive
on the back foot, gets ready to pull but the ball wasn't that short outside off and readjusts with more of a straight ball through mid-off
outside off, Tendulkar waits and eases down on the crouch, opening the face to work it to gully
huge width outside off, and quite full, Tendulkar waits, and reaches out away from his body to steer it high over the slips
yet another wide for Johnson, this one down off
wideish outside off again, but just to say legal - this one's left
straighter, but still outside off, good length and played off the back foot into the ground towards short point
defended straight on the front foot back to the bowler this time
short ball outside off, lots of width, and some good fielding again in the off-side ring, Ponting this time gets his hands to it in front of point
down the legs this time, another wide
a better line for Johnson, just across the right hander and defends on the front foot
straight ball on off, defended back down off the back foot
a good ball from Clark there, asking the question just outside off, the seam scrambled, hits a good length and curls out a touch on its way through, the batsman playing at it on the front foot
outside off, played down to the gully and they run through
on off, good length, and defended on the front foot
pushed into the short covers and they run through, good pressure with that running
short ball just outside off, turned off the back foot to deep backward point
overpitched on off, driven straight back hard past the bowler
short ball boomed across him, straight, and the batsman sways away, the ball nearly brushing this upper chest on its way through. Good ball, there
overpitched outside off, the batsman gets right down to the drive to the covers
a full ball on middle and off, just a push to mid-on and they run through quickly
outside off, a hint of width and some room to cut down into the point region, the batsman pulling the power out of the shot, there
on middle and leg, whipped round behind square this time
down leg, the batsman ducks, waiting for the ball to go through above him, but it went wider

short ball outside off, helped over the top with an upper cut over the slips, Johnson slides to try to keep th eball in and there's a quick debate about whether he was connecting with the rope when the ball touched his boot
comes back in off the seam from outside off, the batsman works off the back foot out in front of point
outside off, pushed into the covers off the back foot and they run through
outside off, the batsman is tempted to come and meet the ball with a push outside off, Clark nearly picking up the edge
just to say outside off, cut down towards Gilchrist who takes off his glove, races out to meet it and throws down the non-striker's sticks, quick work but no cigar, the batsman was back in
rolls his fingers over the ball, looking to get it to cut back in outside off, but worked into the covers
some width outside off, Tendulkar pushes into the covers this time
outside off, the ball sits up a touch short and the batsman's eyes light up, then he chops down an inside edge from a back-foot cut
doesn't get hold of a pull shot which he takes from outside off towards midwicket, more of a force than anything, he's there too early, the ball not coming on off the surface
very wide outside off, cuts out at it but doesn't get the edge, that would have been a soft ending
outside off, waits for the slower ball and leans into the drive wide of mid-off, almost through the covers
outside off, cut down into the ground into the covers, not much power on that shot
full delivery outside off, pushed to mid-on
a short ball on off, hooked down off the eyes towards midwicket
outside off, driven out to the covers
on middle and leg, pushed too straight, the batsman gets over it and works it in front of square
shortish ball outside off, opens the face and works it down to third man
short ball outside off, dabbed down to third man and watched it all the way
up there on middle and off and whipped out to midwicket

on middle and leg, turned off the legs in front of midwicket, a mix-up between the batsmen as Bracken went down to pick up the ball, Hopes bluffing, pretending he was sliding for it. Tendulkar gets back into his crease
a wide down leg
wide outside off, cut hard to Symonds in the covers
outside off, pushes out on the front foot and a thick outside edge skews out wide to Lee at third man who scrambles and rolls to keep it in play and returns well
width outside off and cut hard through backward point, the ball a touch uppish but nowhere near a fielder and the ball rockets on
width outside off, cut down to the fielder in the gully this time
on middle and leg, well waited and indeed weighted, and driven out to mid-on
gone through him outside off, Tendulkar plants his front foot forward, Gilchrist takes the ball just over the stumps and goes for the stumping, but the back foot was in throughout
on the legs, pushed out to square
short ball moving away outside off, the batsman rushes his hands at it but it's already on its way
stops on the shot, the batsman popping up towards mid-off as the ball comes in on middle, the leg-cutter, and Hopes races round to take a straightforward, palms-up catch
on the legs, clipped with a jump behind square and they come back for two
wide outside off, that's another one for him
short and straight, played down off the back foot to gully
short on leg, the ball is turned down off the legs into short midwicket
short ball angled down leg and there's another wide
short ball outside off, played down off the back foot towards one of the three third men
pushed through well now he's bowling to a fellow left-hander, a good line and length and some encouraging outswing, good carry, too
full ball on off, Gambhir plays it down off the legs through a wide fine leg
fired across him outside off, driven out square to Hussey at deep point
outside off, worked down well off the back foot to fine third man
pushed across him outside off, cut down to third man
shortish ball outside off, guided down well off the back foot to wide third man and a wild throw to the non-striker's end from Johnson allows an extra run
a play and a miss outside off, good ball, there
comes in outside off, pushed out to mid-on where there's a misfield by Ponting this time
pitches on leg and moves off the seam towards off, Gambhir knocks it down and they run through a well-judged single
outside leg, Gambhir climbs straight into him with a drive through long-on, coming out of the track to meet the ball
driven out to the covers
stays round the wicket, Tendulkar knocks it off the legs to short midwicket
forces it quite wide across him, Gambhir cuts it out behind point
slight width outside off, the batsman waits and forces it out behind point

full ball with plenty of room, driven out to mid-off, Clarke moves across and takes out Tendulkar with a tackle, pulling him down. Tendulkar finds it amusing, and that's the sort of tactic we use in beach cricket
short ball outside off, he cuts so hard but somehow Clarke cuts it off, lightning reactions there
cuts deeper this time, wide of Clarke and again Bracken does as well as he did earlier to chase round and dive out hard to cut it off just inside the rope
defended on the front foot this time
outside off, cut down to third man
pushed across him outside off, driven out hard to mid-off
outside off, driven out to mid-off, Lee throws at the non-striker's but jujst misses this time
defended on the front foot this time
outside off again, Gambhir comes down the track and drives very hard indeed high and out towards long-on where Johnson, his face full of set-jawed determination, takes the catch
turned off the legs behind square for a quick single
big loop up there on the pads, in front of off, pushed out to short midwicket on the front foot
Yuvraj wastes no time at all, superb timing and all eye there as he steps out and drives hard and flat over straight long-on
slower ball angles in on leg, and turned out to midwicket
pushes across the left hander, who drives into the covers and they take the easy single
outside off, good length ball, turned down off the back foot to gully
outside off, left alone down the channel this time
right up there on off, defended on the front foot this time
a full delivery in line with off, defended on the front foot back to mid-off
right up there on off, steered away to backward point off the back foot
beaten outside off, wide ball, chased through
right out there on off, defended down on the front foot
comes outside off again, defended on the front foot
his first  movement is forward, then he rocks back to cut down behind point
on the legs, turned off behind square for an easy single
comes down the wicket to drive a ball from off out through mid-on
stands on the back foot and goes into the line of one of off, defending down comfortably
well bowled, the slower yorker fires through outside off and the ball shoots inside the line of the bat, and on to the keeper
left alone outside off this time
turned down off the hips to short midwicket
outside off on a good length, pushed out to the covers on the front foot and the cover fielder cuts it off well
waits on the back foot for the ball which comes on off, is pushed down just square on off and they shuffle through, pumping their bats as they go and Clarke does the fielding
turned in on a good length on off, pushed off the back foot into the covers
turned off the legs to fine this time, an easy steer
width down leg, Tendulkar goes down after it but is a touch too late and the umpire signals the wide
stands firm on the front foot and pushes to the covers
steps back, exposing his stumps as he sets himself for a firm drive to the covers
driven back to the bowler who dives out to stop it
full up there, driven out to mid-on quietly
a short ball on the legs, helped back down off the hips to short square leg, Lee the fielder, whipping it back in
a full ball speared in on middle and leg but flicked away on the leg-side
slower ball, a full toss on off and Yuvraj lifts that high over straight long-on with a full-blooded drive, good timing
across the left hander who pushes off the back foot to the covers
bends it in to him on line with off, pushed into short midwicket now
outside off, cut off the back foot down to deep third man
full delivery on off, pushed out to short midwicket
gives it some extra air on off, driven back to the off-side
up there and defended on the front foot. "Bowling, Puppy," says Gilchrist (possibly "Pup, here", you never know)
opens the face and beats the man at backward point
driven hard back to the bowler who dives out to stop it
wristed off into the leg-side to round off a good over from the bowler
short ball outside off, follows it with an open bat, but could have played a hard cut, there
knocked out to mid-on to bring Yuvraj back on strike
good loop on leg, Yuvraj drives out to mid-on where there's a rare slip from Clarke
outside off and smashed hard up and wide of long-on, taking one bounce over the rope, good clean hands there
defends sturdily and quietly on the front foot in line with off stump this time
on the legs, turns a bad delivery down to fine leg and the bowler gets away with it
swivelled in on off, driven back out to the bowler
backs away behind the stumps and drives simply into the covers
right up there on off, defended on the front foot, quietly now
rips it in on a line with off, defended on the front foot. "Bowling, Pupster," says Gilchrist this time
worked out square this time
Clarke tosses it in short, Tendulkar comes out of his crease, looking for the firm drive, doesn't quite get hold of it
on off stump, driven out to long on
full ball down the legs, goes for the sweep shot, plays it round too late
outside off, comes out and sweeps down on one knee and that has gone fast and flat
defended on the front foot this time
superb piece of fielding from Clarke at midwicket
worked out well to deep midwicket this time
short ball outside off, Yuvraj takes the bait and goes hard with a pull down Hayden's throat at deep midwicket
drags it down short and wide and it's cut out through the covers this time
outside off, flaps at that one really, but the outside edge travels through third man and goes on the way, quite a deliberate shot
outside off, comes down a touch and drives out to the covers
curls in on middle and leg, turns out to short midwicket
up there on middle, driven out to the covers
width outside off, cut down to third man off the back foot
defended on the front foot this time
outside off, touched with a cut off the back foot behind point
down leg and Dhoni does very well to get any bat on that, turning it back past the keeper, hitting it like a croquet mallet
pushed out to the covers this time
full delivery on off, pushed off the back foot behind point
turns it a touch outside off, the batsman shuffles back, exposing his stumps, and forces back out through the covers
on off, driven out to the covers for a gentle single
driven from middle out to long-off
the reverse sweep, quality, takes it from leg and really gets hold of that, a great shot behind square
defended this time
turned out to the legs to bring up the 200
backs away to show his stumps and cuts straight to the fielder in the covers
came back in from outside off, defended on the front foot
walks across the stumps and knocks the straight ball over his left shoulder down to straight fine leg and they come back for three
driven forward to long-on, good timing, just easing it out for a single
up there on off, pushed out to the alert man at cover who doesn't allow them to even think of the single, nevermind attempt it
a fuller delivery, pushed out off the back foot to the covers
tidy ball on off, pushed back to the bowler on the back foot to round off a fair over at this stage of proceedings
driven out to mid-off quietly
comes down the track and pops up a soft push towards Ponting at short mid-on who takes a few steps, takes off and dives forward to take a brilliant catch
pushed back to the bowler on the front foot who picks it up easily
driven back hard to the bowler this time
driven out to mid-off
aimed in at the stumps but pumped well away with a cut off the back foot
defended on the front foot this time
outside off, let it go through to the keeper
squares into a defensive in line with off
angled in on off, driven out to the covers
came back in outside off, pushed out to mid-off
short ball outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man
hangs it out there outside off, the batsman drives on the up to the covers and Symonds snaps a sharp chance
pushed off the back foot behind point for a quick single
round the wicket, defended on the front foot with a dig out in front of his toes
a hint of turn outside off, driven out to the covers
width outside off again, driven hard to the covers this time
full toss on off and Clarke gets away with it as the batsman controls a push-drive back to him
shortish ball on off helped round the corner to fine leg for a quick single
pushed across him, steered out to point off the back foot
full ball on middle and off, driven back to the bowler who dives on to it
on middle, driven out straight to long-off
width outside off, looked to push it down the track, missed it outside off
driven out to long-off this time
round the wicket, the batsman squeezes a hard cut outside off, connecting only with air
overpitched on middle and leg from round the wicket, driven out to long-off for an easy single
on middle and leg from over the wicket, a hint of rise, and squeezed out to short midwicket
short ball outside off and Irfan comes right out of his crease and gets hold of it with a firm pull behind square
fired in at the legs, brushed out there to short midwicket
full ball outside off, driven back to Bracken who snaps it up
outside off, full ball, driven out to mid-off and Clarke nearly, nearly took the stumps there
full again turned round off the legs to fine
driven out to mid-on, a firm shot, almost a pull, the fielder gets it and sends the batsman back into his crease
well bowled, up there, driven back to the bowler who dives and cuts it off
pushed right up there and defended on the front foot
plenty of width outside off, the batsman mistimes the shot, a would-be force into the off-side
a yorker on off, driven back hard to the bowler who cuts it off well
round the wicket, fires it flat down off
forces it back in in line with off, driven back out to long-off now
drags it a touch short outside off, forced through mid-on
full ball, driven back out on the back foot to the covers, well cut off by Symonds
short ball outside off, Irfan heaves it over to deep midwicket and Hussey comes round to do the fielding
short ball outside off, a mishit off the base of the bat initially looks like he will hole out, instead it travels all the way straight over the bowler with a full drive
pushed forward this time
rocks back and swipes out to the covers on the front foot
low full toss driven hard and straight out to long-off
stays over the wicket, short ball and pulled into midwicket
outside off, Irfan goes for the cut and misses it
outside off, cut out square to point
slower ball cleans him up, the batsman looks to pull it off the back foot, completely times it wrongly and  the ball comes in a touch to take off and middle
comes right out on off, and turns it back behind square leg
comes outside off and drives cleanly out to the on-side, fairly straight
fired a flat ball outside off, too quick for the batsman to react
chipped out a full ball from in line with middle, doesn't get enough middle on it and Clarke takes a comfortable catch
short ball, Praveen Kumar shoulders into the ball allowing it to hit him square in line with the stumps
again he shoulders into the ball, didn't offer a shot and that runs on for leg-byes
moves back across the stumps and goes for a huge cut, the ball racing through point
a better length and following the batsman back behind the stumps who gets an inside edge down to fine leg
not much doubt about this one, Harbhajan looking to pull and it would have hit middle stump squarely, not much thinking required from the umpire, there
outside off, pushes hard at it away from the body, you couldn't call it a convincing shot and it races past Gilchrist's glove to bring up the 250
slower ball, Kumar launches high over towards long-off and the ball lands safe, plugging a touch in the deep
fired it up on a good length, defended in front of middle
low full toss aiming in on leg and the batsman forces out to the covers where Ponting holds on, the ball coming out of the sun, and he lost it for a second

slower ball, a play and a miss outside off, nearly a stumping for Gilchrist, who takes the bails, the batsman falls over, Gilchrist takes the stump out of the ground and appeals, but he was back in safe
slower ball on the legs, Sreesanth scoops it out to square leg
full ball driven out to long-off and they come back well for two

inn2.comm: bit of shape outside off, starts on off and moves away, left alone
short of a length, moving away a bit and Gilchrist is away, off the back foot, through the covers for a couple, confident start

and he's walked! Praveen Kumar has done the trick again, starts outside off and moving a shade away, tentative poke from Gilchrist and the ball kisses the outside edge on its way to the keeper, big appeal and he is on his way, Praveen can't contain his excitement, dream start for India, Gilchrist walks off to a rousing ovation, probably for the last time in a one-dayer
outside off and he's shouldered arms, good probing line from Praveen, he's highly rated in the domestic circuit
defended down the ground
short of a length, straight to him, pushed to cover
swing straight away, full and on middle, moving into Hayden's pads, he tries to flick it away but too cramped for room
follows up with one outside off, shoulders arms, some late swing there, Australia have a job on their hands here
full and outside off, 134.9kph, good pace there, Hayden digs out one that's almost yorker length, the fielders are swooping down quick, egging Sreesanth on, bit of lip here
full and on middle, smashed down the ground with a touch of arrogance, on the front foot and thumped past the bowler, past mid-off and through to the fence, no chance for the fielders there
full outside off, holds back the pace a bit, chipped tentatively to the leg side and takes off for a single, attempted direct hit but he makes his ground
short of a length on middle, turned to the leg side, sloppy effort from Harbhajan at midwicket allows them a single, a few boos going around the ground, surely that's not for Ponting
bit of inswing for Kumar, Ponting watches it closely before tucking it to the on side, straight to the fielder
more inswing, 127.6kph, jagging back from off, strikes Ponting on the pads and a muted appeal but that was going high, the ball nestles in Ponting's pads

got 'em, now then, now then, short and outside off, Ponting goes for the pull and can't get hold of it, spoons an easy catch to Yuvraj at mid-on, that seemed to stop on him a bit, Yuvraj can't contain his excitement, Kumar is cock-a-hoop, what a start for him, someone must be planning a party in Meerut today

huge appeal, that was perilously close, what a first-baller to get, swinging in sharp from outside off, strikes him in front but the height was probably in question, Kumar is causing plenty of problems here, Tony Hill thought about it but said, 'No'.
outside off, that was a bit straighter, left alone from Clarke, he's keeping him guessing here
more movement, this time swinging into the right-hander, pushed back down the ground, back to the bowler, Kumar is making the ball talk here
good length and outside off, 137kph this time, he's running in a bit more smoothly now, Hayden shoulders arms
full and on middle and off, touch of movement into the left-hander, punched to the covers

dropped, full and outside off, nice bit of swing away from the left-hander, Hayden swishes and the ball takes the edge, Dhoni dives to his left but can only get a slight deflection, strikes Tendulkar on his left shoulder as the ball trickles away, Tendulkar in pain, Dhoni can't believe he fluffed that
full and outsde off, driven hard to cover
good length outside off, moving away, fine swing, lets it go
full and on off, driven confidently down the ground, Sreesanth can't get his hand to it, they pick up a couple
short of a length, 126kph, moving away, Hayden lets it go, swing is doing the trick here
moving away again, this time it's well telegraphed, Hayden decides to let it go
that comes in, he's playing the three-card trick well, two away and one in, moves a bit too much, Hayden gets it away behind square for a couple
straight this time, good-length ball, defended cautiously down the ground
full and swinging again, Hayden is foxed big time, flashes outside off but it's moving away so subtly, beaten all ends up, Hayden can only acknowledge the fine ball
lets that go outside off, starting too much on the off, fine over
short of a length, 140.8kph, rising on the batsman, played on the toes, back down the ground
short of a length, outside off, cranking up the pace towards 145kph, defended off the back foot, sharp ball that, two short ones in a row
good-length ball but that's on the pads, tucked away in front of square for a couple
on the pads again, Clarke is making the most of this, turned away easily
outside off, moving away and Clarke throws his bat at it, it's in the air and finds the gap, Sreesanth struggling with his line here
outside off and Clarke doesn't need to play at that, lets it go
good length and outside off, Hayden watches it closely before pushing it to the covers, can't find the gap, though
on the pads, turned away to the leg side for a single
short of a length and Clarke spanks it through covers, gets the timing right, watching the ball closely, he's a fine batsman this Pup
well outside off, sliding too far away, left alone, wide called and rightly so
full and outside off, tapped away in the gap through covers, on the back foot, not as much swing as earlier now
full and outside off, pushed to the off side
better rhythm from Sreesanth, 131kph, slightly brings down the pace, on and outside off, driven to mid-on, Sreesanth slightly more wide of the crease here
full and on off again, punched forcefully to mid-off, straight to the fielder, the ball is striking the middle of the bat more often now
short of a length, outside off, patted to the point region and a firm 'No', Clarke looking to settle the nerves here
short of a length and outside off, quicker this time, that takes a thick outside edge and races away to third man, Clarke took his bottom hand off the bat in the last moment
full and outside off, left alone, no harm done, a buzz enveloping the ground now, lights in full force too
similar ball outside off and Hayden watches it closely and shoulders arms, better over from Sreesanth this time
good-length ball outside off, Clarke pushes off the front foot, straight to cover
slightly back of a length, stopping on Clarke, he tries to force it through the off side and a thick edge trickles to fine leg, Kumar knows that was close
signs of the ball stopping on the batsman, Hayden watches it eagerly and pushes it down the ground
swing that time but that's sliding too far down leg side, Clarke pounces on the chance and deflects a full one to fine leg, the fielder is too square and he can't reach it
short of a length and outside off, pushed back to mid-off

castled! that one kept low and Kumar's straighter one beats Clarke's defences, slightly short of a length, Clarke tries the pull but that ball shoots through, it's straight and rocks back off-stump, big blow for Australia, signs of up and down, India on a roll now

a huge, curdling call from Sreesanth, bending down in imploration (if that's a word) as Hayden comes forward to a good-length ball which comes back in from the seam and would perhaps have clipped off-stump but the benefit was given
pushed out on the front foot with a forward defensive
pushed way way across him from over the wicket down wide
good-length ball outside off, just left alone
down wide outside off again, carbon copy of earlier in this over
ooh, an outside edge streaks (oops) through just short of the slips, pushed over the wicket across him
a full delivery, the batsman pushes down and an outside edge runs down towards deep third man
a big leave just outside off, on a good length
fired up there on off, Symonds defends solidly on the front foot
on middle, clipped into the legs, the ball goes to short midwicket
...but not this time, banging in a short ball on leg and Hayden comes down and bullies the ball all the way through midwicket with a muscling pull
outside off, defended back towards mid-off and they run through quickly
pushed forward on the front foot, Hayden diving home
big width outside off and Symonds cuts hard through point

some swing outside off, and Symonds could have inside-edged that back on to the stumps a la Clarke if he wasn't careful, Sreesanth comes haring down the track to kick on, the ball only half a metre from the sticks.  The batsman was well safe
stands firm and defends into the short cover region
defended this time
cut down forward once more
full toss at hip height, pushed on the front foot to short midwicket
round the wicket, the batsman pushes forward, Sreesanth rushes up, tries to pick up the ball and gets half a hand on it, enough to stop it down dead anyway
some swing in towards Symonds who waits solidly and pushes the ball from in line with off to midwicket on the front foot
banged in down off, a touch short in line with the stump and it's helped on its way with a firm pull out to deep midwicket and up comes the 250
a shortish ball, cut down to point off the back foot
full and swinging up to the right hander who pushes into midwicket
a full delivery, driven straight forward this time
a touch of width outside off, Symonds cuts it down off the back foot to point for an easy single, and what would have been a very risky double
a full swinging ball down off this time, left alone
outside off, cut down to point, straight to the man there
short and wide outside off, cut behind point
some swing in towards Symonds and he offers a play and a miss, his heart no doubt in mouth for a second
left alone outside off this time
reaches up on to his back foot and the ball shoots past the outside edge, Symonds prodding down
pushed through outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
waits on middle, looks to pull it, but forces it back forward towards the bowler
shortish ball outside off, cut out to point off the back foot this time
pushed down the leg side this time
width outside off, Hayden looks to drive hard, but picks out the fielder at cover and without much power
full ball on off, swings away from Hayden this time
full ball on off, inside-edged out to square with a firm pull
stands on the back foot and pushes to the covers firmly
turned off the legs with a firm shoulder of a push out to mid-on
swing in to the left hander but a bit too far and Hayden muscles behind square off the thigh
a full toss cut out to deep point and they look for the extra run but Symonds turns it down
good swing in on a decent length, the batsman defends on the front foot
tight ball on off, pushed out to the covers, more defensively than anything
short ball outside off, cut down to the man at point who picks it up easily
width outside off, Hayden pulls it round to short midwicket on the back foot
width outside off, and some swing, driven out to the stumbling cover and they get a single
full ball swinging back in from outside off, yorker even, defended on the front foot
goes for the yorker again, driven out to mid-off, Yuvraj, who gets a hand on the ball but they manage to sprint through
wide outside off once more, flat-batted hard out to mid-off
up there on the legs, driven out to long-on
full ball on off, driven out to mid-off, well flighted at 83kph
snuck past Hayden and the leg stump, he was nearly bowled then but it was called wide, a touch harshly perhaps
outside off, and Hayden can't connect, driving back into the ground
turn past him, the inside edge nutmegging him and going out on a square leg trajectory
but Hayden wins this mini-battle, coming down the track and meeting the ball which had been tossed up on off, driving straight down the line through long-on
faster, flatter, up there on off and forced the batsman to defend on the front foot
forced across him, quite wide and Symonds edges hard off the base wide of first slip
very wide outside off, short too, but Symonds went after it with a back-foot upper cut
slower ball rolled past the outside edge, Symonds waits on the back foot and lets it go through this time, at chest height
outside off, waited on the back foot and forced the drive to mid-off and they decide to "Wait on" but not a restaurant capacity
outside off, some width and Symonds chances his arm with a flowing drive over the ring, wide of the fielder at backward point
right up there on middle and the batsman brings his wrists down quickly on a push to midwicket
lets that one go wide down off for another wide
just outside off, a good length, driven well to the covers but can't find a run
rocks on to the back foot and is watchful in cramping the ball into short midwicket
good loop on off, the batsman comes out and shapes to push back forward, which he does, defensively
turns back in from outside off and the batsman works the ball to short midwicket
good length ball up there on off, but it's eased back out to mid-on for an easy clip of a single
fired in on the legs now and clipped to fine leg
a huge shout for what looked to be quite a handy lbw decision, but Umpire Taufel immediately turned it down
well bowled up there on off, tucked into the midwicket region on the front foot
on off and that's positively drilled through mid-off on the front foot
defended down on the front foot, a good reply from Irfan, forcing him to play a good-length ball in line with off
tight line on off, pushed back out to the covers on the front foot this time
forced across him from over the wicket, the batsman waits on the back foot and eases it down way behind point
width outside off and drilled on the front foot with a firm drive through cover
good loop on middle, right up there and dipped down just in front of middle, defended down
more defending on the front foot, clamping the ball under the bat
down on one knee and looks to sweep it out to leg, and indeed does so
full ball on off, defended down, trapping the ball under the bat
on the legs, Symonds drives out to short cover, Raina the 12th man, doing the job
a hopeful appeal around the off-side, pushed outside to the covers
short ball outside off, Hayden gets away with a huge edge as he goes for the booming drive, the ball racing wide of Dhoni and travelling on its way

outside off, more width, and Hayden drives hard to the covers where the man (Yuvraj) picks it up and throws it back in hard, misses the throw-down and it goes on for four overthrows, Sreesanth can't get it on the boundary
short ball and straight, ducked under the bouncer well
digs out the would-be yorker in line with off with a push-drive out to the covers
a defensive steer out forward
outside off and Hayden goes aerial, easily clearing the ring on off and the ball is driven on through extra cover
full ball on middle and leg, pushed down into the on-side
extra loop on the legs, driven out to mid-on this time
good flight again on middle, driven back out to short midwicket
turned back in on the legs and Hayden clips it out for another fifty, his third in a row
turned off the legs to square and they run through
good loop on middle and off, eased out to mid-on
...famous last words, Symonds spanks the ball from short outside off right over long-on
a better ball, flatter, fuller, and Symonds defends it back down
on th legs, cut down off the back foot to gully, there's a mix-up but Hayden gets back into his crease in time
whirred in outside off, it turns back a touch and is defended on the front foot
a standing sweep shot, turned the ball into the ground and down to the leg gully
on leg, turned down to short square leg
pushed right up there on the front foot
overpitched a touch outside leg, but worked straight to the fielder ar midwicket
on middle and leg, rises up and is knocked back out in front of midwicket
got him! Symonds pushes into the covers, Yuvraj does the work, throwing the ball back in to Harbhajan who takes the stumps as Hayden can't back in at the non-striker's end
looped up there on middle, Symonds somehow manages to work the ball down to third man
outside off, turns back a fair way and traps Symonds on the pad low and in front of middle and off, the batsman bending over the ball and it would have gone on to take middle
full delivery outside off, the batsman comes on the front foot and drives out on the leg-side
down leg and worked down there
full ball on off, driven out to mid-on
big loop outside leg, and a hopeful, overexcited appeal there
good loop again and defended on the front foot
more good loop, an appeal but more in hope than expectation, Hopes is unmoved and so is the umpire
looped across him outside off
pushed past him again outside off, played out
good ball in line with middle, defended on the front foot
a huge bark of an appeal from Harbhajan as the ball comes in on off but the batsman gets an inside edge
comes out forward and defends on the front foot
defended on the front foot
more defence on the front foot
asked the question as the ball came in from outside off
on the legs, swept out to deep square
good loop, but on the legs and Hussey glances well through fine leg and Australia do well to come back for three
on middle and leg, turned back to middle and the batsman gets some bat on it
wide outside off, the batsman goes down on one knee and shapes to cut hard to point, but misses the ball
good loop up there on leg, driven out to midwicket
pushed up there deviously on off, a dipping delivery, but the batsman is in defensive control

comes down the track and pushes up off the legs, Dhoni chases hard, fast as he can in keeping pads, towards leg gully, takes the catch, a great dive, and calls for the catch, but Umpire Taufel says no, rightly
on the legs, turned round to short fine leg
outside the legs, turned back in to the left hander who in turn pulls it back out in front of midwicket
forces him on to the back foot and he plays back down off the back foot
driven out to mid-off
big loop up outside off, driven out to the covers this time
right up there on middle, defended on the front foot
right up there and stretches out to drive, being kept quiet here
overpitched outside off, driven out to deep mid-off
pushed on the front foot to the covers
right up there on off and there's a big appeal as the ball comes in from outside off but hit him outside the line
driven out to the covers on the front foot
right up there in line with middle, defended tidily on the front foot
short ball outside off, pulled very hard indeed through midwicket, that was hit with immense power
outside the legs, swept round to short fine leg
rigth up there outside off, driven out to mid-on and they race through
pulled out to midwicket
outside off, driven hard to mid-off this time
bowled very well indeed past him, beating Hussey's outside edge as he pushes forward looking for the cover drive
on middle, Hussey reverse sweeps down to third man and they chase down two
whirred in flat and well on off, the batsman stabs forward on the front foot this time
good movement in on off, driven back out to the covers
just a bit short outside off and cut out to point
pulled out to deep midwicket this time
well bowled, beating the inside edge and could have deflected back on to the stumps
round the wicket by the way, swirls in just outside off, driven out to mid-off
up there on middle and off, turned back out to midwicket
pushed him back into the crease, on the back foot, and he forced out to mid-off
full ball on off, driven out to long-off for an easy single
comes down to push the ball to short midwicket on the front foot
outside off, turned back in from a good length, pushed out to short midwicket
forced across him outside off and he pushes into the covers
outside off, the batsman steps out and defends hard on the front foot
well bowled again, forcing the forward defensive into the covers
defended
defended again
steps out and pushes right back to the bowler
driven out to mid-off this time, Yuvraj keeping the pressure on here
width outside off, cut out to point
comes out and whips the reverse sweep out, very wristily indeed and the ball races away through deep backward point
defended this time
tried to work this one in the gape past cover
pushed out off the back foot to long-off but they can't come back for the second
looped up there on middle and leg, Hussey sweeps behind square and they come back for the second
right up there on off, cut down towards third man
well bowled, fired in up there on off and the batsman defends forward this time
pushed off the legs in front of square and they come back for the second
looped up on off, worked out square to bring up the fifty partnership
offers the full face of the bat defensively outside off, an inside edge comes back down
defended forward
right up there on off, driven back out softly to mid-on and they jog through the single
defended again with a push out straight and they choose not to have the single
a slightly slower ball outside off, pushed to point off the back foot
looped in on middle and swept well in front of square for four, the crowd love it, cheering and whistling
defended on the front foot back towards the bowler
comes back in from outside off, the batsman steps forward and the ball rolls up the bat and on
on middle and off, driven out to mid-on for the single
big loop on middle, Hussey pushes back out defensively
right up there on off, defended on the front foot back towards the bowler and there's no run
shortish ball just outside off, the batsman jabs a defensive press off the back foot to gully and it's well picked up
width outside off and cut hard off the back foot to point, Praveen sweeping round and picking up the ball inside the rope
on to the legs and pushed out straight to midwicket
on middle and leg, tucked off the legs to midwicket on the front foot
width outside off, Hussey pushes out a single to deep midwicket
very wide outside off
much better ball, tighter on off, defended down off the back foot into the covers
short ball on the legs, tucked off to square this time
some swing away from the left hander, and width, driven out to the covers and there's a misfield from Raina
pushed up there on off, driven out to long-off
more width outside off and cut into the gap at point
outside off, cut to backward point this time and the sweeper prevents them taking a second, which they had certainly thought about
width outside off, worked very wide towards the deep extra cover boundary where Praveen does the fielding

tucked down off the back foot to the gully and they shuffle through a risky single, Hopes could have been out at the non-striker's end there, ah, replays show he would have been safe even if it were direct
a long hop which deserved the treatment and was spanked round the corner through fine leg
a full toss on off and Hussey can't capitalise, cutting straight to the man at gully
short outside off, cut out behind point and they charge through
width and short outside off and Hussey cuts hard off the back foot, sending through a thick snick of an under edge to Dhoni who took it and started celebrating
a swing and a miss from Hopes, who nearly takes the edge as he tries to pull a short from outside off, but lost control
on the back foot, driven back out to the bowler
dropped, diving to his left, a tough one to call as he made that into a chance, getting a hand in the covers
down the legs, tucked off for a single
the single, driven out to mid-on this time
short ball outside off, defended down off the back foot
drags it down a touch short on outside off, pulled round hard just wide of mid-on
short ball, width outside off, cut hard to point
down the legs, swept down behind square this time
pushed back just wide of the bowler and they take the single
outside leg, swept hard behind square and they run through and come back
outside leg, Hopes gets down on one knee and takes the single, stealking the strike, too
driven back out to long-off for a gentle single
popped to midwicket, in the air but just wide of the fielder, they get a quick two
attempted yorker, dug out towards square leg for a single
slower ball from Kumar, Hopes left his crease early but that's wide and he can't reach it, the umpire doesn't call a wide, maybe because of Hopes coming down the track so far
what a shot, full-toss is spanked back down the ground with immense power, waist-high and he bludgeons it back past the bowler, burnt the grass on its way
slower ball and it's pulled away with force, Gambhir tries to get his hands to it but it's over him for four, 12 off the over, good one for Australia, Hopes playing a special knock
tossed up on the legs, swept down to fine leg
short ball outside off, cut off the back foot for a single to bring Hopes back on strike
well bowled, a quicker one at 104kph, coming back in to the batsman from outside off and he defends on the front foot
on off, swept out to deep midwicket and Lee puts his arm out to Hopes, telling him not to come back
outside off, driven to mid-off this time
they scramble a leg-bye as it's swished round to fine leg
the yorker dug back out over his head to straight long-off
full toss on off and the batsman got away with it, with a pull to midwicket
rolls it in at 132.3kph, the batsman tries to cut out off the back foot to point
cleans him up this time with the slower one, Lee going for the huge pull across the line and the ball crashes on to the sticks
outside off, curled in an attempted yorker, Johnson inside edges back out square
comes outside off and booms hard towards the covers, but misses the ball and that rounds off another impressive spell from the composed Praveen
round the wicket and Johnson flashes away from the body, a huge edge goes wide of the keeper and the ball runs on
well bowled up there on off, Johnson gets right behind the ball and defends forward
pushes it on off, and turned out square for a quick two
dipping full toss on leg, tucked out in front of square to bring Hopes back on strike
outside off, Hopes goes to drive to the covers and gets the inside edge which goes past Dhoni
full toss on the legs, swept round out to deep backward square leg
full ball on off, driven out straight to long-off and it was hit so hard they can only take the single

got him! A big edge through to Dhoni off the back foot, Sreesanth gets another wicket in similar fashion, a short ball way outside off, Johnson goes for the huge pull to midwicket and the under edge slicks through to the keeper
on middle, driven out to mid-on for a quick single
outside off, very well bowled slower ball, the batsman looking to hockey-style sweep it standing up from outside off, a good legbreak there
short ball outside off and Hopes scythes a full-blooded pull up and over long-on, wide of it, that travelled flat and hard for a maximum
full toss, driven out hard to mid-off to take the strike
a big drive, and an outside edge loops over wide to a very wide third man, around very deep backward point
full delivery comes in slow on off, Bracken swipes it up to midwicket where a pedalling Chawla runs over and takes it over his head at the second grasp
swinging yorker dug out to long-off and some good running there has them home
outside off and Hopes drives it up to Chawla at mid-on who takes the catch calmly and India win!
